cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use DogLM, please cite it as below."
title: "DogLM: an open benchmark for spontaneous pet-the-dog mechanics in LLM-generated games"
abstract: >-
  DogLM measures whether a large language model, asked to generate a video game
  that contains a dog but given no instruction about the dog, spontaneously lets
  the player pet it. Each model generates small browser games from product
  requirements documents that mention a dog only as background; the generated
  code is then scored for whether the player can interact with the dog.
authors:
